<a name="wp1159530"> </a><h2 class="pTitle">
Overview
</h2>
<hr />
<a name="wp1159546"> </a><p class="pBody">
The DSC100 Servo Controller positions a hydraulic or pneumatic actuator based on a position demand signal received from field device. The DSC100 can positions a single-coil or dual-coil actuator using single or dual position feedback devices. The position demand signal of DSC100 can come from Network, Serial Port, 0-25 mA, or all of them. A software program running on a Personal Computer (PC) allows the user to easily configure, monitor  and calibrate the DSC100.
</p>
<a name="wp1170687"> </a><p class="pBodyRelative">
<img src="images/1_Overview-DSC100_Connection.png" height="421" width="825" id="wp1170685" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="0"/>
</p>
<a name="wp1170683"> </a><p class="pBody">
The DSC100 Configurator is used to configure, calibrate, adjust, monitor, and troubleshoot a DSC100. The Configurator runs on a PC and communicates with the DSC100 through a serial connection or Ethernet connection. The serial port connector is a 9-pin sub-D socket and uses a straight-through cable to connect to the PC. Tri-Sen offers a 485 converter to 9-pin Serial Adapter kit if needed for new computers that do not have a 9-pin installation serial connector. This kit contains a 485 converter, software, and a 1.8 m serial cable. Ethernet connector is the standard RJ45 sockets and crossover cable. 
</p>
<a name="wp1170687"> </a><p class="pBody">
The DSC100 is configured by using the DSC100 Configurator to create a file that is then loaded into the DSC100 Controller. The DSC100 Configurator can also read an existing configuration from a DSC100 Controller into the configuration file editor.
</p>


